			<small class="commentmetadata"><a href="#comment-93111" title="">May 11th, 2013 at 10:08 pm</a> </small>

			<p>I tried installing Debian 7 on an old 32 bit laptop, but it didn&#8217;t work.  Then I tried Linux Mint 14 and that didn&#8217;t work either.  So, I tried Linux Mint 13 and Success!  It turns out that the laptop has a Pentium M processor which doesn&#8217;t support a PAE kernel.  The Pentium M processor is i585 architecture rather than i686.  So, I guess that&#8217;s why it didn&#8217;t work.  Just wanted to pass that on in case anyone else has this problem.  No more support for these older processors?  Yikes!</p>

			</li>
		

	
